{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 15:28:15.275441", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Solution submitted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"leaf_router_0_0\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"bgp_asn_misconfig\"]\n\nRecommended remediation (not submitted, for operator action):\n- On leaf_router_0_0 change BGP local AS from 65800 to 65200 to match spine peers:\n  - Edit configuration: under router bgp, set \"router bgp 65200\" and ensure neighbors remain configured to peer with remote-as 65200 on the spine-facing adjacencies.\n  - Alternatively, update spine neighbor remote-as to 65800 if that ASN is the intended one for the pod (less likely given other devices use 65200).\n- After config change, verify:\n  - show ip bgp summary on leaf_router_0_0 -> neighbors reach Established.\n  - show ip bgp on spines -> 10.0.0.0/24 is learned and installed.\n  - From other hosts, ping 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0) to confirm reachability.\n\nIf you want, I can provide exact CLI commands to apply the fix and verification steps.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2261, "output_tokens": 250, "total_tokens": 2511, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
